com.github.misberner.buildergen.annotations

Annotation Type Option


  • @Retention(value=SOURCE)
@Target(value=PARAMETER)
public @interface Option
    Annotation for providing information about an option used in a builder.
    Author:
    Malte Isberner

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      String defaultExpr
      An expression (specified as a string) to use as a default value for this option.
      String getterName
      The name of the getter for this option.
      String name
      The name of the option.
      String setterName
      The name of the setter for this option.
      String value
      The name of this option.
      Visibility visibility
      The visibility of the attribiute for this option.
      String withName
      The name of the with method for this option.

    • Element Detail

      • value

        public abstract String value
        The name of this option. This value is only taken into account when the name() attribute is set to the empty string. If this value is also empty, the default option name (see above) will be used.
        Default:
        ""

      • name

        public abstract String name
        The name of the option. If this field is set to the empty string, the value of the value() attribute is used, if this is specified and non-empty. Otherwise, the default option name (see above) will be used.
        Default:
        ""

      • defaultExpr

        public abstract String defaultExpr
        An expression (specified as a string) to use as a default value for this option. Note that all references to Java elements (including the instantiated type) that are not in the same package as the generated builder must be fully qualified. Generic type parameter names may be used as declared. If the empty string is specified, the default value will be taken from the defaults class (see GenerateBuilder.defaults()), if available. Otherwise, Java's default policy for non-final field initialization will apply (false for booleans, zero for numeric primitive types and null for reference types).
        Default:
        ""

      • setterName

        public abstract String setterName
        The name of the setter for this option. If set to the empty string, the default policy (see above) applies. If set to AccessorMethods.SUPPRESS, no setter will be generated for this option.
        Default:
        ""

      • getterName

        public abstract String getterName
        The name of the getter for this option. If set to the empty string, the default policy (see above) applies. If set to AccessorMethods.SUPPRESS, no getter will be generated for this option.
        Default:
        ""

      • withName

        public abstract String withName
        The name of the with method for this option. If set to the empty string, the default policy (see above) applies. If set to AccessorMethods.SUPPRESS, no with method will be generated for this option.
        Default:
        ""

      • visibility

        public abstract Visibility visibility
        The visibility of the attribiute for this option. If Visibility.INHERIT is specified, the visibility declared in the GenerateBuilder annotation will be used.
        Default:
        com.github.misberner.buildergen.annotations.Visibility.INHERIT
